data.text:
Janice Dickinson appeared in the season 8 episode "Still Charmed and Kicking." While Paige Matthews was disappointed at the turnout to her memorial, she glamoured into Janice and claimed the two were friends.

Biography[]

Janice Doreen Dickinson was born on February 15, 1955 in Brooklyn, New York. She is an American model, fashion photographer, actress, author and agent. Janice considers herself to be the first ever supermodel. One of the most successful models throughout the 1970s and 1980s, she expanded her profession to reality television in 2003 by being hired by Tyra Banks to judge for four cycles on America's Next Top Model. She also opened her own modeling agency in 2005, which was documented as The Janice Dickinson Modeling Agency.

Personal life[]

Janice has been in relationships with Warren Beatty, Sylvester Stallone, Jack Nicholson, Liam Neeson, Sir Mick Jagger, Ronnie Wood, Kelly LeBrock, Prince Albert II, Roman Polanski, Dolph Lundgren, Grace Jones, Bruce Willis, Frank Zappa, John Cusack, David O'Hara, and Jon Lovitz.

She has been married 3 times - to Ron Levy, Simon Fields (1987–1993), and Albert B. Gerston (February 1995 – 1996).

Janice has two children, Savannah and Nathan.
